packageJSON.name: SeqPlots
packageJSON.description: An interactive tool for visualizing NGS signals and sequence motif densities along genomic features using average plots and heatmaps.

releases.name: SeqPlots electron GUI v3.0.12c
releases.body:
This release contains _C. elegans_ (ce10) and _D. melanogaster_ (dm3) genomes. To download additional genomes follow the instructions here: http://przemol.github.io/seqplots/#genomes-managment

## Installers:
- **[SeqPlots-3.0.12.dmg](https://github.com/Przemol/seqplots_electron/releases/download/v3.0.12c/SeqPlots-3.0.12.dmg)** - macOS installer - **Mac OS X 10.9 or higher required**
- **[SeqPlots_Setup_3.0.12.exe](https://github.com/Przemol/seqplots_electron/releases/download/v3.0.12c/SeqPlots_Setup_3.0.12.exe)** - MS Windows installer - **64bit Windows 7 or higher required**
- **[SeqPlots-3.0.12-x86_64.AppImage](https://github.com/Przemol/seqplots_electron/releases/download/v3.0.12c/SeqPlots-3.0.12-x86_64.AppImage)** - Ubuntu Linux application - **Ubuntu 16.04 LTS required**

## Zip/Tarballs containing source code:
- **Source Code** - compiled with node.js

## Linux installation notes:

**Only Ubuntu 16.04.1 LTS (Xenial Xerus) is supported by SeqPlots desktop app. Please update your system: http://releases.ubuntu.com/16.04/ or install R/Bioconductor version of SeqPlots: http://bioconductor.org/packages/seqplots**

GUI version requires following libraries:
libgtk2.0, libxtst6, libxss1, libgconf-2-4, libnss3, libasound2, libgfortran3

To install them under Ubuntu type in the console:

```
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install libgtk2.0 libxtst6 libxss1 libgconf-2-4 libnss3 libasound2 libgfortran3
```

Using the AppImage on Ubuntu Server requires following packages:
desktop-file-utils, xdg-utils, zenity

```
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install desktop-file-utils xdg-utils zenity
```

Before running SeqPlots the application should be made executable, either by _right click => Properties => Permissions => Allow executing file as program_ or running following command:

```
chmod a+x SeqPlots-3.0.12-x86_64.AppImage
```

releases.name: SeqPlots electron GUI v3.0.11
releases.body:
This release contains _C. elegans_ (ce10) and _D. melanogaster_ (dm3) genomes. To download additional genomes follow the instructions here: http://przemol.github.io/seqplots/#genomes-managment

## Installers:
- **SeqPlots-3.x.x.dmg** - installer for macOS (Mac OS X 10.9 or higher required)
- **SeqPlots-3.x.x.exe** - MS Windows portable installer (64bit Windows 7 or higher required)
- **SeqPlots.Setup.3.x.x.msi** - MS Windows global installer (64bit Windows 7 or higher required)
- **SeqPlots-3.0.11-x86_64.AppImage** - Linux AppImage application/installer

## Zip/Tarballs:
- **SeqPlots-3.x.x-mac.zip** - zipped app for macOS
- **SeqPlots-3.x.x-win.zip** - MS Windows zipped application (64bit Windows required)
- **SeqPlots-3.x.x-linux.zip** - Linux zipped application (teased on Ubuntu 16.04 LTS)

## Zip/Tarballs containing source code:
- **Source Code** - compiled with node.js

## Linux installation notes:

Linux version requires following libraries:
libgtk2.0, libxtst6, libxss1, libgconf-2-4, libnss3, libasound2, libgfortran3

To install them under Ubuntu type in the console:

```
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install r-base
sudo apt-get -y install libssl-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev libssh2-1-dev

sudo /usr/bin/env Rscript -e 'source("http://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R"); biocLite(c("seqplots","devtools")); devtools::install_github("przemol/seqplots",build_vignettes=FALSE);'

```

Using the AppImage files might require to install following packages:
desktop-file-utils, xdg-utils, zenity

```
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install desktop-file-utils xdg-utils zenity
```
